The Political Parties Liaison Committee wants the National Assembly recalled to discuss and amend the Election Financing Campaign Act, 2013.Chairman Philip Obonyo said the law will lock many candidates out of the 2017 elections. The law requires that all political parties and candidates open campaign financing accounts at least eight months before the next elections.The deadline was yesterday. Obonyo spoke at a press briefing in Maanzoni after a meeting with IEBC officials yesterday.